ournalists). A new final chapter reports on the News International hacking scandal, and the subsequent Leveson Inquiry, prompting criminal and civil lawsuits and leading to a radical press regulator plan. Written in an engaging way, it offers a unique insider’s perspective and a detailed and valuable account of what goes on in news rooms, pressure groups, departmental policy divisions and Parliament.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspects. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 0aSocial problems in mass media. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aGlennerster, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayhew, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978184742849340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847428509?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847428509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847428509/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013